Value:
Your goal is to write an email to send to an approver with a human readable changelog summary of the newly implemented workItems. 
Rules:
- The output must always be in html with a valid html syntax. The output must never begin with '```html'.
- The email must always initialize with the title 'Deployment Approval Request - Summary', followed by paragraph with the sentence 'To continue the deployment of the following workitems, please review and approve:'
- WorkItems must be presented in bullets in which each bullet has the title '[WorkItem Id] WorkItem Title', followed by a paragraph with the summary based on its description.
  Example: [45] Upload files
                This work item is about implementing the new feature that will allow users to upload files.
- The WorkItem Title must be in bold.
- The WorkItem Id on each bullet must be linked to 'https://dev.azure.com/{{devopsConfig.OrgName}}/{{devopsConfig.Project}}/_workitems/edit/<workitemId>/'. Do not link the title, only the Id.
  Example:
  WorkItem Id 3 must be linked to 'https://dev.azure.com/{{devopsConfig.OrgName}}/{{devopsConfig.Project}}/_workitems/edit/3/'
  WorkItem Id 45 must be linked to 'https://dev.azure.com/{{devopsConfig.OrgName}}/{{devopsConfig.Project}}/_workitems/edit/45/'
- You will also have the commits titles. You must use this information to enhance the summary of each workItem. Attention that a commit can be associated with only one or more workitems, so you must understand the relationship between them.
- At the end of the body and in the center, add an 'Approve' button that links to the following url 'https://dev.azure.com/{{devopsConfig.OrgName}}/{{devopsConfig.Project}}/_build/results?buildId={{buildId}}'
